Better solution:

  def all_titles(books)
    books.map {|book| book.name }
  end

or even: 

  def all_titles(books)
    books.map(&amp;:name)
  end

Why not, for array of book titles:

  def all_titles( books )
    books.map { |book| book.name }
  end

Cleaner, simpler... Inject isn't very useful here, it just ads extra syntax for no reason :)
